data.text:
New Orleans Saints wide receiver Jamal Jones (89) runs out a pattern after catching a pass during practice Wednesday, Aug. 16, 2006, at their football training camp at Millsaps College in Jackson, Miss. Jones is a testament to the concept of mind over matter, having spent the summer running routes alone in a park or on an empty high school field, hauling in passes thrown by the quarterback in his head, in an effort to gain an opportunity to earn a roster spot, a feat Jones has accomplished. (AP Photo/Rogelio V. Solis)
